The President made calls to the families of the victims of the Arizona tragedy and will continue to do so throughout the week. He assured them that everything is being done to investigate the incident. The President received updates on the investigation from John Brennan and spoke to FBI Director Mueller to express his appreciation for their work. The President also made calls to Representative Gifford's husband, Governor Jan Brewer, Speaker John Boehner, Representative Eric Cantor, Representative Nancy Pelosi, Representative Steny Hoyer, Representative James Clyburn, Representative Ed Pastor, the family of Christina-Taylor Green, the family of Gabe Zimmerman, Senator Jon Kyl, and Senator John McCain.